The paper deals with the problem of estimating functionals of discrete distributions, which is a topic that falls under the purview of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistics (cs.ST). The paper also uses concentration inequalities and approximation theory, which are techniques commonly used in data science (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
